<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 07 at 2:37AM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Sullivan, northeastern Unicoi, Johnson, Carter and southeastern
Washington Counties through 415 AM EDT...
At 337 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pine Crest, or 8 miles south of Elizabethton, moving northeast at
50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Elizabethton, Mountain City, Hampton, Unicoi, Damascus, Hunter, Neva,
Laurel Bloomery, Limestone Cove and Sadie.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
